orange-box (1.57-0ubuntu1) utopic; urgency=medium

  * debian/control, debian/postinst, debian/preinst,
    etc/maas/bootresources.yaml => usr/lib/orange-
    box/inc/bootresources_1.6.yaml, usr/bin/orange-box-setup-nat,
    usr/lib/orange-box/inc/bootresources_1.5.yaml, usr/lib/orange-
    box/inc/squid.conf:
    - provide a transparent caching working squid proxy by default
      on node0
    - no longer depend on squid3
    - we are going to overwrite the squid-deb-proxy config file
      with our own caching squid proxy conf (copied from Canonical's
      UDS's conference mirror caching proxy)
    - transparent proxy runs on 3128, though we will also run an
      explicit proxy on 8000 (squid-deb-proxy's port) for compatibility
    - use some ping tests, to ensure outbound network connectivity
    - install separate bootresources configuration for both maas 1.5 and 1.6

