    usr/bin/orange-box-setup-nat, usr/bin/orange-box-status-all-nodes,
    usr/lib/orange-box/inc/squid.conf:
    - change the default Orange Box network from a 10.14.4.0/24 to a much
      larger 10.14.0.0/16, to accomodate Landscape and the Cloud installer
      and lots more DHCP addresses (think, kvm and lxc instances)
    - the MAAS endpoint and gateway remains 10.14.4.1
    - the AMT nodes remain 10.14.4.11-19
    - the MAAS managed DHCP range expanded from ~50 addresses to 25K,
      from 10.14.100.1 - 10.14.199.254
    - feed the AMT ip address in when adding nodes
  * debian/control, debian/preinst:
    - add /etc/network/interfaces stanza for a VLAN to access the
      network switch configuration interface on 10.90.90.90
  * debian/dirs, debian/postrm, usr/bin/orange-box-add-virtual-nodes,
    usr/bin/orange-box-purge-everything:
    - move the vm backing disks to /var/lib, out of ubuntu home
    - remove the backing disk images on purge

